{{Quote|An inspiring tale of bravery from Verinti this week, as thirteen-year-old citizen Mav Gatta saved her entire homestead from raiders using survival techniques she had seen on the hit holodrama ''Troops''. The young hero has been granted a full scholarship to the Imperial Academy.|Dorna Parros, HoloNet News|audio=Verinti-Outlaws.flac|<ref name="Outlaws" />}}
'''''Troops''''' was a popular [[holodrama]] viewed by the citizen [[Mav Gatta]].<ref name="Outlaws" /> In [[3 ABY]],<ref name="Date">{{OutlawsDate}}</ref> the thirteen-[[Standard year|year]]-old Gatta used survival skills she had learned from watching the show to save her [[Mav Gatta's homestead|homestead]] from raiders, earning her a full scholarship to an [[Imperial Academy]] from the [[Galactic Empire]]. ''Troops'' was then mentioned by [[Journalist|reporter]] [[Dorna Parros]] in coverage of Gatta's story on the [[HoloNet News]] later that [[Standard week|week]].<ref name="Outlaws" />

==Behind the scenes==
''Troops'' was mentioned in the [[2024]] [[Massive Entertainment]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Outlaws]]''. It shares its name<ref name="Outlaws" /> with [[Kevin Rubio]]'s [[1997]] fan film [[w:c:starwarsfans:TROOPS|TROOPS]], which depicts [[stormtrooper]]s as parodies of the law enforcement officers featured in the television series [[Wikipedia:Cops (TV program)|COPS]].<ref name="TROOPS fan film">{{WebCite|url=https://www.theforce.net/fanfilms/story/TROOPS_Ten_Years_Later_112870.asp|text=TROOPS: Ten Years Later|author=[[Kevin Rubio]]|date=2008-03-01|work=[[TheForce.net]]|archivedate=20230313150241}}</ref>

